      "component": "Maladaptive Strategies",
      "item": "Avoid Police",
      "explanation": "For a 75-year-old widowed female with an accident trauma, avoidance of police is clinically unusual and lacks clear connection to the trauma type. Accident survivors typically avoid accident-related triggers (vehicles, locations, etc.), not law enforcement, unless the accident involved police negligence or investigation trauma, which isn't indicated."
    },
    {
      "component": "Maladaptive Strategies",
      "item": "Mirror Checking",
      "explanation": "Persistent mirror checking is more characteristic of body dysmorphic concerns, eating disorders, or appearance-focused OCD than typical PTSD following an accident. This strategy doesn't align with common post-accident avoidance patterns (e.g., avoiding driving, certain locations, or medical settings)."
    },
    {
      "component": "Maladaptive Strategies",
      "item": "Avoid Exercise",
      "explanation": "Avoidance of exercise is plausible if the accident was exercise-related (e.g., sports injury) or if physical activity triggers somatic memories, but without that context, it's an unusual maladaptive strategy for a general accident trauma in an elderly patient."
    }
  ]
}
